ğŸ§  What is OOP?

**OOP (Object-Oriented Programming)** is a programming approach based on **objects**.

ğŸ“Œ Objects contain:

* **Properties** (data)
* **Methods** (functions)

ğŸ“Œ OOP helps in:

* Code reusability
* Better structure
* Easy maintenance

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§± Core OOP Concepts

1. Object
2. Class
3. Encapsulation
4. Inheritance
5. Polymorphism
6. Abstraction

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“¦ Objects in JavaScript

An object represents a **real-world entity**.

```js
let user = {
  name: "Saakshi",
  age: 21,
  greet() {
    console.log("Hello " + this.name);
  }
};

user.greet();
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ—ï¸ Classes in JavaScript

A **class** is a blueprint for creating objects.

```js
class User {
  constructor(name, age) {
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
  }

  greet() {
    console.log("Hello " + this.name);
  }
}

const user1 = new User("Saakshi", 21);
user1.greet();
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” Encapsulation

Encapsulation means **binding data and methods together** and controlling access.

```js
class BankAccount {
  constructor(balance) {
    this.balance = balance;
  }

  deposit(amount) {
    this.balance += amount;
  }
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Keeps data safe
ğŸ“Œ Prevents misuse

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¬ Inheritance

Inheritance allows one class to **inherit properties & methods** of another class.

```js
class Person {
  speak() {
    console.log("Speaking");
  }
}

class Student extends Person {
  study() {
    console.log("Studying");
  }
}

const s1 = new Student();
s1.speak();
s1.study();
```

ğŸ“Œ Promotes code reuse

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” Polymorphism

Polymorphism allows **same method name** with **different behavior**.

```js
class Animal {
  sound() {
    console.log("Animal sound");
  }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
  sound() {
    console.log("Bark");
  }
}

const dog = new Dog();
dog.sound();
```

ğŸ“Œ Method overriding

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ«¥ Abstraction

Abstraction means **hiding implementation details** and showing only essentials.

```js
class Car {
  start() {
    this.#engineStart();
    console.log("Car started");
  }

  #engineStart() {
    console.log("Engine running");
  }
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Focus on *what* not *how*

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”’ Private Fields (`#`)

Used to restrict access.

```js
class User {
  #password;

  constructor(pass) {
    this.#password = pass;
  }
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Accessible only inside class

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¬ Prototypes (Behind the Scenes)

JavaScript uses **prototype-based inheritance**.

```js
function Person(name) {
  this.name = name;
}

Person.prototype.greet = function () {
  console.log("Hello " + this.name);
};
```

ğŸ“Œ Classes internally use prototypes

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ†š OOP vs Procedural Programming

| OOP              | Procedural     |
| ---------------- | -------------- |
| Object-based     | Function-based |
| Reusable         | Less reusable  |
| Easy to maintain | Hard to scale  |

